   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Well, since this is a fun deck, I will not get too deep into strategy here. I will just explain what makes this deck so fun.  <br>
This deck is so fun because it all revolves around gaining mass amounts of energy. Your basic goal is to gain as much energy onto the Pylofuf as you see fit by using your magi&#39;s refresh, then either Impact it or use the Mushroom Hyren&#39;s Sanctuary to bring its energy back on to your Magi, in which case you&#39;ll usually want to use Cataclysm or a maxed out Thunderquake to clear the opposing board.  The Mirror Pendants and Sorreah&#39;s Dream&#39;s are in the deck so that you can use your Magi&#39;s Refresh Multiple Times a turn to ensure the growth of the creature everybody loves to hate, Pylofuf. Since the Pylofuf will be growing to enormous proportions here, it will naturally become a prime target for Shockwaves and the likes. That is why I have planned to include 3 Uuuuum...NO, to prevent such horrible, horrible things from happening. Anyways, I have not played the deck as of yet, but it looks like its going to be a blast to play once I get it going.  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
